{"id": "EUVD-2025-30848", "enisaUuid": "5631cfa0-e7d3-335d-9424-31bf0df732ba", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nfuse: Block access to folio overlimit\n\nsyz reported a slab-out-of-bounds Write in fuse_dev_do_write.\n\nWhen the number of bytes to be retrieved is truncated to the upper limit\nby fc->max_pages and there is an offset, the oob is triggered.\n\nAdd a loop termination condition to prevent overruns.", "datePublished": "2025-09-23T06:30:28", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-12T21:31:32", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-39888", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/623719227b114d73a2cee45f1b343ced63ce09ec", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9d81ba6d49a7457784f0b6a71046818b86ec7e44"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-39888", "GHSA-jgjw-jx49-6q8j"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1b95d5be-dedb-3e68-9561-a2cfe7ba8267", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17-rc6"}, {"id": "3a7d8e5a-23c6-338a-9f55-c87f8af5101b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17"}, {"id": "3b81f7ed-6f58-304d-9a4d-125bb4a0926c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.16"}, {"id": "5b095a61-d3d0-3235-b541-0674d01472e9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "76f8c218-88a1-398c-83c3-d61f8e705754", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16.8"}, {"id": "7e5d519a-499d-3253-adca-8e76eaf8ef8c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3568a956932621cafadafc8b75fcf6dc06555105 <9d81ba6d49a7457784f0b6a71046818b86ec7e44"}, {"id": "f97a808f-99f2-35e8-b1d9-6bef8e78bbbd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3568a956932621cafadafc8b75fcf6dc06555105 <623719227b114d73a2cee45f1b343ced63ce09ec"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "38e87bbc-4145-3c6a-93d6-f5fa0a2f4e1f", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}